<!DOCTYPE html>

<html>

<head>

    <title> CKart</title>

    <link rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" href="css/cart.css">

    <link rel="stylesheet" type="text/css"
        href="https://stackpath.bootstrapcdn.com/font-awesome/4.7.0/css/font-awesome.min.css">
    <!-- Swal -->
    <script src="//cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/sweetalert2@11"></script>
    <script src="sweetalert2.all.min.js"></script>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="sweetalert2.min.css">
    <!-- Button -->
    <link href="//netdna.bootstrapcdn.com/bootstrap/3.1.0/css/bootstrap.min.css" rel="stylesheet" id="bootstrap-css">
    <!-- <script src="//netdna.bootstrapcdn.com/bootstrap/3.1.0/js/bootstrap.min.js"></script> -->
    <script src="http://ajax.googleapis.com/ajax/libs/jquery/1.7.1/jquery.min.js" type="text/javascript"></script>
</head>

<body>

    <!-- As a link -->
    <nav class=" navbar-light bg-light"
        style="background-color: #4843a3;height: 4em; color: white; padding-left: 42em;">
        <a href="/" style="    float: left;
        margin-left: -38em;
        margin-top: 1em;
        color: white;">Home</a>
        <a class="navbar-brand" href="/" style="font-size: x-large; font-weight: bold; color: white;">CKart</a>
    </nav>

    <div class="col-md-12 row" >

        <div style="background-color: white; width: 25%; height: 20rem; margin: 3rem 0rem 0rem 5rem;" class="col-md-3">
            <div style="display: flex; padding: 2rem; align-items: center;">
                <img class="_3X2gOt" height="50px" width="50px" src="images/avatar.svg">
                <div>
                    <p
                        style="font-size: small; margin-left: 2rem; font-weight: 100; display: flex; flex-direction: column;">
                        Hello,</p>
                    <p style="padding-left: 2rem; font-size: large;">
                        <%= user.name %>
                    </p>
                    <!-- <hr> -->
                </div>

            </div>

            <div style="    padding-left: 3rem;">
                <a style="text-decoration: none;color: #0075ff;" href="/my-orders">
                    <h3 style="font-size: 17px;">My Orders</h3>
                </a>
                <a style="text-decoration: none;color: #0075ff;" href="/my-wishlist">
                    <h3 style="font-size: 17px;">My Wishlist</h3>
                </a>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="col-md-4"
            style="background-color: white;  width: 40rem;  height: 100%; padding: 2rem; margin: auto;  margin-top: 5rem;border: 1px solid;margin-right: 5rem;">

            <form action="/profile-edit" method="post">
                <p style="color: red;"> <%= error %> </p>
                <h3 style="font-size: large; font-weight: 500;">Personal Information</h3>
                <input type="text" value="<%= user.name %>" style="height: 50px; font-size: 14px; border: 1px solid #d7d2d2; width: 27rem; padding-left: 20px;  outline: none;
                border-radius: 2px;" name="name">&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp

                <!-- <input type="text" value="" style="height: 50px; font-size: 14px; border: 1px solid #d7d2d2;     outline: none;
                border-radius: 2px;"> -->
                <br>
                <h3 style=" font-size: large; font-weight: 500;">Your gender</h3>
                <% if(user.gender=="Male" ) { %>
                    <input type="radio" style="margin-top: 4px; " name="gender" value="Male" checked>&nbsp Male &nbsp
                    <input type="radio" name="gender" value="Female"> &nbsp Female &nbsp <br>
                    <% } else { %>
                        <input type="radio" id="rad" style="margin-top: 4px; " name="gender" value="Male">&nbsp Male &nbsp
                        <input type="radio" id="rad" value="Female" name="gender" checked> &nbsp Female &nbsp <br>
                        <% } %>
                            <h3 style="    font-size: large;font-weight: 500;" >Email address</h3>
                            <input type="email" 
                                style="height: 50px; font-size: 14px; border: 1px solid #d7d2d2; width: 27rem;    padding-left: 20px;  outline: none; border-radius: 2px;"
                                placeholder="<%= user.email %>" name="email" value="<%= user.email %>">

                            <h3 style="    font-size: large; font-weight: 500;">Mobile Number</h3>
                            <input type="text"
                                style="height: 50px; font-size: 14px; border: 1px solid #d7d2d2;  padding-left: 20px;  outline: none; border-radius: 2px;"
                                placeholder="<%= user.number %>" name="number" value="<%= user.number %>">

                            <button type="submit"
                                style=" background-color: #4f27f9; color: white; margin-left: .5rem; width: 7rem; height: 3rem; border-radius: 7px; border: 1px solid;">Save</button>
                                
                            </form>
                            
        </div>
        <div class="col-md-4"
            style="background-color: white;  width: 37rem;  height: 100%; padding: 2rem; margin: auto;  margin-top: 5rem; border: 1px solid;padding-bottom: 4rem;">
            <form action="/password-change" method="post">
                <p style="color: red;"> <%= passworderror %> </p>
                <h3 style="font-size: large; font-weight: 500;">Old Password</h3>
                <input type="password" value="" style="height: 50px; font-size: 14px; border: 1px solid #d7d2d2; width: 27rem; padding-left: 20px;  outline: none;
                border-radius: 2px;" name="oldpswd">&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp
                <br>
                <h3 style="    font-size: large;font-weight: 500;" >New Password</h3>
                <input type="password" 
                    style="height: 50px; font-size: 14px; border: 1px solid #d7d2d2; width: 27rem;    padding-left: 20px;  outline: none; border-radius: 2px;"
                    placeholder="" name="newpswd" value="">
                <h3 style="    font-size: large;font-weight: 500;" >Confirm Password</h3>
                <input type="password" 
                    style="height: 50px; font-size: 14px; border: 1px solid #d7d2d2; width: 27rem;    padding-left: 20px;  outline: none; border-radius: 2px;"
                    placeholder="" name="confirmpswd" value="">
                <br><br>
                <button type="submit"
                    style=" background-color: #4f27f9; color: white; width: 27rem; height: 3rem; border-radius: 7px; border: 1px solid;">Change Password</button>
                    
                </form>
        </div>
        

            <br><br><br>
        <div class="col-md-12"
            style="background-color: white;    height: 100%; padding: 2rem 9rem; margin: auto;  margin-top: 3rem;">

            <h3 style=" font-size: large; font-weight: 500;"> FAQs </h3>
            <p> What happens when I update my email address (or mobile number)?</p>
            <p> Your login email id (or mobile number) changes, likewise. You'll receive all your account related
                communication on your updated email address (or mobile number).</p>

            <p> When will my account be updated with the new email address (or mobile number)?</p>
            <p> It happens as soon as you confirm the verification code sent to your email (or mobile) and save the
                changes.</p>

            <p> What happens to my existing account when I update my email address (or mobile number)?</p>
            <p> Updating your email address (or mobile number) doesn't invalidate your account. Your account remains
                fully functional. You'll continue seeing your Order history, saved information and personal details.</p>

            <p> Does my Seller account get affected when I update my email address?</p>
            <p> Ckart has a 'single sign-on' policy. Any changes will reflect in your Seller account also.</p>

        </div>

    </div>

</body>
<script>
    function changePassword(){
        document.getElementById("changePassword").style.display = 'block';
    }
</script>

</html>